<subSubSection id="693D46A8B3300E3137746A8F8A0AF3A9" pageId="0" pageNumber="271" type="notes">
<paragraph id="703C3927B72FC3D0670F6D47A14B4066" pageId="0" pageNumber="271">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="33C899FADE72FCB9383A9EC52FDC151B" pageId="0" pageNumber="271">
A recently described species from the Northern Central East of Madagascar (
<bibRefCitation id="CB950912EDD39BD4FF57FA73F347730E" author="Hutter, CR" journalOrPublisher="Zoosystematics and Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="271" pagination="483 - 495" refId="B26" refString="Hutter, CR, Andriampenomanana, ZF, Andrianasolo, GT, Cobb, KA, Harinarivo, J, Abraham, RK, Lambert, SM, 2022. A fantastic new species of secretive forest frog discovered from forest fragments near Andasibe, Madagascar. Zoosystematics and Evolution 97: 483 - 495" title="A fantastic new species of secretive forest frog discovered from forest fragments near Andasibe, Madagascar." volume="97" year="2022">Hutter et al. 2022</bibRefCitation>
) that is genetically and morphologically distinct by a reddish iris, gray to whitish vocal sacs and large femoral glands with 7-8 distinct, externally visible gland granules, and a dorsal skin texture consisting mainly of sharp ridges rather than of rounded tubercles (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="2319ABDB6FCA792DE1AE24D91DF6727D" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figure 11. Adult male of Gephyromantis marokoroko (KU 343230) from Vohidrazana in life, in A dorsolateral, B dorsal and C ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/vz.72.e78830.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/688681" pageId="0" pageNumber="271">11</figureCitation>
). A tibial gland is absent. According to the original description, SVL is 24.0-27.0 mm in males and 23.9-24.6 mm in females. The species is so far only known from several sites near Andasibe: Belakato in Andasibe-Mantadia National Park, Vohimana, Vohidrazana (type locality) and Tavalobe near Vohidrazana. We reanalyzed the call of 
<taxonomicName id="08BDA07538F895DB1122F99E98FEE577" genus="G." lsidName="G. marokoroko" pageId="0" pageNumber="271" rank="species" species="marokoroko">
<emphasis id="AFF19686FA434E7505B9DD84B6A2C278" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="271">G. marokoroko</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to ensure full comparability with the call descriptions of all other 
<taxonomicName id="9FB5DDE5AE795D363C0789A8C61145E1" authorityName="Dubois" authorityYear="1980" class="Amphibia" family="Mantellidae" genus="Laurentomantis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Laurentomantis" order="Anura" pageId="0" pageNumber="271" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="036CC814CC6D14FAF8ACD8B317C2624E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="271">Laurentomantis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9806850813D9E803FC7A1C80670FB343" pageId="0" pageNumber="271" type="call">
<paragraph id="85C770CD2BE625A891375F7E9B401D91" pageId="0" pageNumber="271">Call.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7F908391320A1262D6F57F53C76FDA9A" pageId="0" pageNumber="271">
The advertisement call was recorded on 6 January 2016 at Vohidrazana (air temperature 20.4°C; call voucher KU 343230 [CRH 1110]). It consists of a series of short distinctly pulsed notes of variable duration (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E5A9A3227E08E4DC044CD65D39F6971C" captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. Audiospectrogram and corresponding oscillogram of a 1000 ms section of an advertisement call of Gephyromantis marokoroko recorded on 6 January 2016 at Vohidrazana." figureDoi="10.3897/vz.72.e78830.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/688682" pageId="0" pageNumber="271">12</figureCitation>
). There is recognizable amplidude modulation within each call, with call energy being greatest at approximately 60% of the 
<normalizedToken id="A124E8E29B1F88A9316EC8A81D4A84B3" originalValue="call’s">call's</normalizedToken>
duration, with initial notes being the least energetic ones. Within calls, notes are repeated at constant intervals. Each note contains a certain number of clearly separated pulses repeated at an approximate rate of 150-170 pulses/second. Numerical parameters of 3 analyzed calls are as follows (range followed by mean 
<normalizedToken id="36473AAE8422C5DAAC7B94964C6F82E6" originalValue="±">+/-</normalizedToken>
standard deviation in parentheses): call duration 557-1203 ms (968.7 
<normalizedToken id="41E4F7D3BDE4176252B8ADCF2C34BB4F" originalValue="±">+/-</normalizedToken>
357.7 ms); note duration 10-26 ms (17.4 
<normalizedToken id="A110A4624F814B46CD66121265D9615A" originalValue="±">+/-</normalizedToken>
5.0 ms); number of notes per call 12-28 (21.0 
<normalizedToken id="E2DCFA94CC4C71200DABA87C5A688C4E" originalValue="±">+/-</normalizedToken>
8.2); note repetition rate within calls 18.2-19.6 notes/second (18.8 
<normalizedToken id="A994ED5D454257DCB390CDD39BA89DBB" originalValue="±">+/-</normalizedToken>
0.6 notes/second); pulses per note 2-5 (3.3 
<normalizedToken id="920D278A7233C33E73155C5BAF5D5A76" originalValue="±">+/-</normalizedToken>
0.9); dominant frequency 2411-2476 Hz (2444 
<normalizedToken id="DD6C636FA4AC8353C17E183C858A028A" originalValue="±">+/-</normalizedToken>
28 Hz), with a second peak of almost equal energy at around 3600-3700 Hz; prevalent bandwidth 1000-5200 Hz. Call repetition rate in short call series (containing 3 calls) approximately 18-20 calls/minute.
</paragraph>
<caption id="55D7FB1F753C48E583D26952B4AE3672" doi="10.3897/vz.72.e78830.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/688681" pageId="0" pageNumber="271" start="Figure 11" startId="F11">
<paragraph id="66898DDE0709096CCB3C7552192B119E" pageId="0" pageNumber="271">
<emphasis id="F715A59909DC584AB32F1EFDB16240A9" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="271">Figure 11.</emphasis>
Adult male of 
<taxonomicName id="31C557534F8216F879370FA97172BA17" authorityName="Hutter, Andriampenomanana, Andrianasolo, Cobb, Razafindraibe, Abraham and Lambert" authorityYear="2022" class="Amphibia" family="Mantellidae" genus="Gephyromantis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Gephyromantis marokoroko" order="Anura" pageId="0" pageNumber="271" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="marokoroko">
<emphasis id="43BF25D64CFA2FF9F851B9DA6A01647A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="271">Gephyromantis marokoroko</emphasis>
